.\" Man page for deepfinder(1)
.\"
.\" Generate with:
.\"   groff -man -Tutf8 deepfinder.1 | less
.\" Install with:
.\"   sudo cp deepfinder.1 /usr/local/share/man/man1/
.\"
.TH DEEPFINDER 1 "2026-05-31" "DeepFinder 3.0.0" "User Commands"
.\"
.SH NAME
deepfinder \- instant file search for macOS
.\"
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B deepfinder
[\fIoptions\fR] [\fIquery\fR]
.br
.B deepfinder
\fIsubcommand\fR [\fIarguments\fR]
.\"
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBDeepFinder\fR is an instant file search tool for macOS, inspired by
Everything on Windows. It maintains a real-time in-memory index of every
file on your system, providing sub-millisecond query latency via an
always-running background daemon.
.PP
When invoked with a search query, \fBdeepfinder\fR sends the query to the
daemon over a Unix domain socket and displays matching results in the
terminal. When invoked without a query, it enters an interactive REPL
mode (v0.6+).
.PP
The daemon is automatically started on first use, or can be managed
manually via the \fBdaemon\fR subcommand. A LaunchAgent can be installed
with \fBinstall\fR to start the daemon automatically on login.
.\"
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-json\fR
Output results as JSON. Each result includes the full path, size,
modification date, and match type.
.TP
\fB\-\-0\fR
Output results separated by null bytes. Useful for piping into
\fBxargs \-0\fR for safe filenames.
.TP
\fB\-\-sort\fR \fIfield\fR
Sort results by the given field. Valid values:
.BR name ", " size ", " date .
.TP
\fB\-\-limit\fR \fIn\fR
Return at most \fIn\fR results. Default: 1000.
.TP
\fB\-\-offset\fR \fIn\fR
Skip the first \fIn\fR results. Useful for pagination.
.TP
\fB\-\-reverse\fR
Reverse the sort order (ascending becomes descending and vice versa).
.TP
\fB\-\-verbose\fR
Show match type and relevance score for each result.
.TP
\fB\-\-serve\fR
Start an HTTP search service instead of performing a query.
Listen on port 7654 by default. Use with \fB\-\-port\fR to specify
a different port.
.TP
\fB\-\-port\fR \fIn\fR
Port number for \fB\-\-serve\fR mode. Default: 7654.
.TP
\fB\-\-help\fR
Show the complete usage text and exit.
.TP
\fB\-\-version\fR
Show the version number and exit.
.\"
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.\"
.SS daemon
Manage the background daemon process.
.TP
\fBdaemon start\fR
Start the background daemon. If already running, reports the PID.
If a stale PID or socket file exists, it is cleaned up before starting.
.TP
\fBdaemon stop\fR
Stop the daemon by sending SIGTERM. Waits up to 5 seconds for graceful
shutdown before reporting an error.
.TP
\fBdaemon restart\fR
Stop the running daemon (if any) and start a new one.
.TP
\fBdaemon status\fR
Show daemon status: PID, uptime, index state, file count, and memory usage.
.\"
.SS config
View and modify runtime configuration. All changes are applied
immediately via IPC to the running daemon.
.TP
\fBconfig get\fR \fIkey\fR
Get the value of a single configuration key.
.TP
\fBconfig set\fR \fIkey\fR \fIvalue\fR
Set a configuration key to a new value.
.TP
\fBconfig list\fR
List all configuration keys and their current values.
.TP
\fBconfig reset\fR
Reset all configuration to default values. Prompts for confirmation.
.\"
.SS install
Install a LaunchAgent plist at
\fI~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.nadav.deepfinder.plist\fR
so the daemon starts automatically on login.
.TP
\fBinstall\fR
Install the LaunchAgent.
.TP
\fBuninstall\fR
Remove the LaunchAgent.
.\"
.SH CONFIGURATION KEYS
.TP
\fBexcludedPaths\fR
Array of filesystem paths excluded from indexing.
Default: \fB["/System", "/Library"]\fR.
.TP
\fBexcludedVolumes\fR
Array of volume mount paths excluded from indexing.
Default: empty (all external and network volumes are indexed).
.TP
\fBindexBatchSize\fR
Number of file records to batch-write to SQLite at once.
Default: \fB100\fR.
.TP
\fBmaxResults\fR
Maximum number of results returned per search query.
Default: \fB1000\fR.
.TP
\fBconfigVersion\fR
Schema version for forward-compatible configuration migration.
Default: \fB1\fR.
.\"
.SH EXIT CODES
.TP
.B 0
Success \(em results were found and displayed.
.TP
.B 1
No results found for the given query.
.TP
.B 2
Daemon error \(em the daemon is not running or could not be reached.
.TP
.B 3
Query error \(em the query syntax is invalid or an error occurred during
search.
.\"
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
\fBdeepfinder hello.txt\fR
Search for files named "hello.txt".
.TP
\fBdeepfinder \-\-json "*.pdf"\fR
Search for all PDF files, output as JSON.
.TP
\fBdeepfinder \-\-limit 10 \-\-sort date "report"\fR
Return the 10 most recent files matching "report".
.TP
\fBdeepfinder \-\-0 "photo" | xargs \-0 ls \-lh\fR
Search for files matching "photo" and pass them safely to \fBls\fR.
.TP
\fBdeepfinder \-\-serve \-\-port 8080\fR
Start the HTTP search service on port 8080.
.TP
\fBdeepfinder daemon start\fR
Start the background daemon manually.
.TP
\fBdeepfinder config list\fR
Display current configuration values.
.\"
.SH FILES
.TP
\fI~/.deep\-finder/\fR
Data directory containing the index database, configuration, logs,
IPC socket, and PID file.
.TP
\fI~/.deep\-finder/index.db\fR
SQLite database with persistent file records. Permissions: 600.
.TP
\fI~/.deep\-finder/ipc.sock\fR
Unix domain socket for daemon IPC.
.TP
\fI~/.deep\-finder/config.json\fR
User configuration file in JSON format.
.TP
\fI~/.deep\-finder/daemon.pid\fR
Daemon PID file for singleton enforcement.
.TP
\fI~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.nadav.deepfinder.plist\fR
LaunchAgent plist for auto-start on login (optional).
.\"
.SH REQUIREMENTS
.TP
\fBmacOS 26 Tahoe or later\fR
Requires Apple Silicon (M4+). arm64 only.
.TP
\fBFull Disk Access\fR
Required for indexing files outside of the user's home directory.
Grant via System Preferences > Privacy & Security > Full Disk Access.
.\"
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR xargs (1),
.BR find (1),
.BR mdfind (1),
.BR launchctl (1)
.PP
Homepage: \fIhttps://github.com/nadav-cheung/DeepFinder\fR
.\"
.SH BUGS
Report bugs at \fIhttps://github.com/nadav-cheung/DeepFinder/issues\fR.
.PP
Known limitations:
\- FSEvents cannot monitor directories without Full Disk Access.
  ~/Documents, ~/Desktop, and ~/Downloads are silently skipped if
  permission is not granted.
\- Not sandboxable due to Full Disk Access requirement. Cannot be
  distributed via the Mac App Store.
.\"
